Reminder
The Blanco Panthers will travel to Yorktown tonight to take on the Yorktown Wildcats.

All tickets must be purchased in advance. To buy your tickets click here -

https://schooleventticketslogin.com/event/view/yorktown-varsity-football-vs-blanco-visitor-tickets

There are 200 tickets for the visitors side. That is 50% capacity. There will be a visitor entrance gate on the Northwest corner of the stadium.

IF you can not make the game, you can watch on Facebook live via the Yorktown Facebook page - https://rb.gy/lazjyw

You can listen to the play by play on the Sun Radio App
or you can go to blancoradio.com

#GoPanthers

Blanco Independent School District
June 16 at 5:00 PM 路

Blanco ISD is saddened at the loss of two of our amazing high school students. They both had contagious smiles and huge hearts. They will be missed. Our hearts and prayers are with the families during this difficult time. Counseling will be available for any student or staff member at BHS from 10:00 AM - 2:00 PM for the next three days (Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday) to assist with grief.

post_text: BHS NEWS AND ALERTS - GRADUATION: Families of seniors with the last name A-Re will enter on the home side gate. Families of seniors with the last name Ri-Z will enter on the visitor side gate near the visitor stands. BISD will provide free face masks for all guests. If you have limited mobility and/or need handicapped seating, please tell your usher when you are being seated. Free water will be provided. We recommend that families take the heat into consideration when planning their arrival time. Seating will be assigned.

Hello, Blanco Community! We are trying to create a Virtual Performance of the Blanco School Song this week to show our unity and determination to make it through this season together. Current students have materials in Google Classroom for this project, but we want to invite all Blanco Band alumni and any musicians in the Blanco community to help us out as well. If you're interested, we have information posted on the High School Band's webpage at http://blancopantherband.weebly.com. Recordings need to be e-mailed in by Thursday, April 16 at 12 pm. If you have an instrument at home, check out those links and get us a recording!

For the past couple of weeks I have been raising caterpillars/chrysalis/butterflies for the EmilyAnn Theatre & Gardens Butterfly Fest  in Wimberley, TX. I raised two cages of butterflies. A video and message from a very smart talented young man at BHS. Mitchell Barnett posted this to his Facebook page and agreed to let BISD use it. Please watch this amazing video.  #PANTHERSSTAYCONNECTED #BlancoSeniors2020

"For everyone missing the way things were, we'll meet again. Maybe not soon, but eventually. Until then, stay safe and healthy - and don't forget we're all in this together. To all the seniors out there: even if we have to finish out the year graduating in a Zoom meeting, don't forget all the great times we had. I miss you guys and hope everyone makes it out of this alright. I know we'll meet again, some sunny day...
 We'll Meet Again - Johnny Cash "- Mitchell Barnett

March 20 at 2:38 PM 路

Everyone reacts differently to stressful situations like COVID-19. You may feel anxiousness, anger, sadness, or overwhelmed. Find ways to reduce your stress to help yourself and the people you care about.

 Learn the common signs of stress.
 Make time to unwind and do activities you enjoy.
 Talk with family and friends by phone, text, or email.
 If you or a loved one is feeling overwhelmed, get support 24/7 by calling 1-800-985-5990 or text TalkWithUs to 66746.

Learn more about stress and coping during the COVID-19 outbreak: https://bit.ly/39UVoEj

post_text: At approximately 8:15 AM we received word from Blanco Police Department that there was a domestic situation happening in close proximity to the middle school. As a precautionary measure to secure our campuses, we have placed BES, BHS and BMS on a lockout status. Lockout status means that all students and staff stay indoors and no one is allowed in or out. We will keep you updated as we know more.

Dear Blanco ISD Families,
Welcome back from the holidays and unfortunately, back to flu and cold season. We have had several confirmed flu cases on each of our 3 campuses. Rest assured that our campus custodians are hard at work disinfecting common touchpoints such as doors, faucet handles, light switches, and computer keyboards at school. You can help reduce the spread of the flu virus at home by encouraging your kids to wash their
hands frequently and not to share food/drink items. 
Thank you for helping to keep our Blanco ISD students healthy!
Robin Johnson, BSN, RN

Blanco Police Department
December 16, 2019 at 4:20 PM 路

The Blanco Police Department recently partnered with the local Dollar General in Blanco to make several local children's Christmas a little brighter. The Dollar General placed a contribution box in their store for their generous customers to donate items. post_text:
On October 16, 2019, Blanco High School participated in both the PSAT and the SAT School Day. The PSAT was given to our Juniors and Sophomores. The SAT School Day was offered to our Seniors. This was the first administration of SAT School Day at Blanco High School. The passing of House Bill 3 made it possible for Seniors to SAT test free of charge here at their home campus! I want to thank the entire Blanco High School community who helped to ensure that test day ran smoothly. Without the help of everyone- custodians, teachers, cafe workers, and our fabulous students we could not have successfully tested the 159 students we did. Thank you, thank you, thank you! Working together makes opportunities possible. Blanco High School, what a great place to be!

Respectfully, Deeanna McLendon, Counselor
text:
On October 16, 2019, Blanco High School participated in both the PSAT and the SAT School Day. The PSAT was given to our Juniors and Sophomores. The SAT School Day was offered to our Seniors. This was the first administration of SAT School Day at Blanco High School. The passing of House Bill 3 made it possible for Seniors to SAT test free of charge here at their home campus! I want to thank the entire Blanco High School community who helped to ensure that test day ran smoothly. Without the help of everyone- custodians, teachers, cafe workers, and our fabulous students we could not have successfully tested the 159 students we did. Thank you, thank you, thank you! Working together makes opportunities possible. Blanco High School, what a great place to be!

Respectfully, Deeanna McLendon, Counselor

Blanco ISD SRO, Steve Harris, organized a law enforcement training for this weekend in an effort to
ensure all local agencies are prepared in case of an emergency. They utilized classrooms at the

Blanco Panther Band
October 6, 2019 at 12:22 PM 路

Congratulations to the Panther Band for a great performance at a very hot and very close contest yesterday. We did not medal, but on a 500 point scale, were only 17 points behind the 1st place school. Our percussion section placed 2nd out of all 3A schools there. The band worked hard this week, and it showed in the performance. We're going to keep working for a knock out performance at UIL in two weeks. To the Top!

Stomp Out Bullying
October 1, 2019 at 11:46 AM 路

Its Bullying Prevention Month! Every October, schools and organizations across the country join STOMP Out Bullying in observing National Bullying Prevention Month. The goal: encourage communities to work together to stop bullying and cyberbullying by increasing awareness of the prevalence and impact of bullying on all children of all ages. Find out more: http://bit.ly/2x29HY3

Blanco Police Department
September 11, 2019 at 10:53 AM 路

The Blanco Police Department would like to thank HEB for being a valued participant in the 2019-2020 school year fill the bus challenge. HEB has been contributing to this project for two years and they are a huge part of the reason it was a big success. We were able to provide the schools within the Blanco ISD with the needed supplies used during the school year. We are looking forward to working with HEB in the future with such projects. Please remember HEB for your shopping needs.
